{"key":"processedPost-13880897","value":{"id":13880897,"first":8851785,"last":13881288,"when":1296492200,"utime":"01/31/11 06:43 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>theshiz777 said:</strong><br />If using wbs cased with verm in a mono tub, and your using a tropic air humidifier, should the humidifier wand be placed near the top of the mono tub or closer to the casing layer at the bottom?&nbsp; And why?&nbsp; Wasnt sure if water droplets landing on top of caps would cause harm.</blockquote><br />Neither.<br />Pumping a humidifier into a small tub will saturate the substrate, ruining performance.&nbsp; A monotub will already be at the correct humidity level.&nbsp; Air exchanges occur through the holes.&nbsp; Monotubs and shotgun terrariums should not use any mechanical means of humidity or air exchange.<br />RR"}}